name: Purpose Lot Identifier Schemename
descriptionLabel: NULL

name: Purpose Lot Identifier
descriptionLabel: Reference (PAR-XXXX) to the part this result is about.

descriptionLabel: NULL

name: Change Reason Code
descriptionLabel: The main reason for the change in the notice compared to the original notice.

name: Change Reason Code Listname
descriptionLabel: The main reason for the change in the notice compared to the original notice.

name: Change Description
descriptionLabel: The description of changes in the notice compared to the original notice.

name: Change Description Language
descriptionLabel: The description of changes in the notice compared to the original notice.

name: Winner Chosen
descriptionLabel: Whether a winner was chosen.

name: Winner Chosen Listname
descriptionLabel: Whether a winner was chosen.

name: Not Awarded Reason
nameLabel: The reason why a winner was not chosen
descriptionLabel: The reason for not choosing a winner.

name: Not Awarded Reason Listname
nameLabel: The reason why a winner was not chosen
descriptionLabel: The reason for not choosing a winner.

name: Contract Conclusion Date
nameLabel: Date of the conclusion of the contract
descriptionLabel: The date when the contract was concluded. Typically, this is the date when the last contractual party signed the contract. However, if no contract is signed, then the date of contract conclusion may correspond to other dates (e.g. the date when the buyer notified the winning tenderer). The date of contract conclusion is always later than the end of the standstill period and the moment when any evidence submitted by the winner has been verified.

name: Contract Identifier
descriptionLabel: An identifier of the contract or, in case of voluntary-ex ante transparency notices and design contest result notices, of the decision. The information in the contract section refers to this contract or decision.

name: Contract URL
descriptionLabel: The uniform resource locator (e.g. the web address) of the contract.

name: Group Framework Maximum Value
nameLabel: Maximum value of the framework agreements in this group of lots
descriptionLabel: It is the re-calculated maximum value likely to be spent for a group of lots within the procedure. This information can be provided when the maximum value of a group of lots is lower than the sum of values of individual lots (e.g. when the same budget is shared for several lots). The value covers all contracts to be awarded within a framework agreement over its whole duration, including options and renewals. The value is re-calculated on the basis of the winners tender or winners tenders.

name: Group Framework Maximum Value Currency
nameLabel: Maximum value of the framework agreements in this group of lots
descriptionLabel: It is the re-calculated maximum value likely to be spent for a group of lots within the procedure. This information can be provided when the maximum value of a group of lots is lower than the sum of values of individual lots (e.g. when the same budget is shared for several lots). The value covers all contracts to be awarded within a framework agreement over its whole duration, including options and renewals. The value is re-calculated on the basis of the winners tender or winners tenders.

name: Group Framework Maximum Value
nameLabel: Maximum value of the framework agreement within the group of lots
descriptionLabel: The maximum value which may be spent in a framework agreement within a group of lots. This information can be provided when the maximum value of a group of lots is lower than the sum of maximum values of individual lots in this group (e.g. when the same budget is shared for several lots). Maximum value means a value covering all contracts to be awarded within a framework agreement over its whole duration, including options and renewals.

name: Group Framework Maximum Value Currency
nameLabel: Maximum value of the framework agreement within the group of lots
descriptionLabel: The maximum value which may be spent in a framework agreement within a group of lots. This information can be provided when the maximum value of a group of lots is lower than the sum of maximum values of individual lots in this group (e.g. when the same budget is shared for several lots). Maximum value means a value covering all contracts to be awarded within a framework agreement over its whole duration, including options and renewals.

name: Concession Revenue Buyer
nameLabel: Estimated revenue coming from the buyer who granted the concession
descriptionLabel: The estimated revenue coming from the buyer who granted the concession (e.g. prizes and payments).

name: Concession Revenue Buyer Currency
nameLabel: Estimated revenue coming from the buyer who granted the concession
descriptionLabel: The estimated revenue coming from the buyer who granted the concession (e.g. prizes and payments).

name: Notice Value
nameLabel: Value of all contracts awarded in this notice
descriptionLabel: The value of all contracts awarded in this notice, including options and renewals.

name: Notice Value Currency
nameLabel: Value of all contracts awarded in this notice
descriptionLabel: The value of all contracts awarded in this notice, including options and renewals.

name: Concession Revenue User
nameLabel: Estimated revenue coming from the users of the concession
descriptionLabel: The estimated revenue coming from the users of the concession (e.g. fees and fines).

name: Concession Revenue User Currency
nameLabel: Estimated revenue coming from the users of the concession
descriptionLabel: The estimated revenue coming from the users of the concession (e.g. fees and fines).

name: Concession Value Description
nameLabel: Method used for calculating the estimated value of the concession
descriptionLabel: The description of the method used for calculating the estimated value of the concession and any other relevant information concerning the value of the concession.

name: Concession Value Description Language
nameLabel: Method used for calculating the estimated value of the concession
descriptionLabel: The description of the method used for calculating the estimated value of the concession and any other relevant information concerning the value of the concession.

name: Winner Size
descriptionLabel: The size of the winner, tenderer or subcontractor (e.g. micro enterprise, small enterprise, medium enterprise).

name: Winner Size Listname
descriptionLabel: The size of the winner, tenderer or subcontractor (e.g. micro enterprise, small enterprise, medium enterprise).

name: Tender Rank
nameLabel: Rank in the list of winners
descriptionLabel: The position of the tender (i.e. whether the tender ended up first, second, third, etc.) in a design contest, a framework agreement with multiple winners (e.g. cascades), an innovation partnership, a competitive dialogue, or another procedure.

name: Country Origin
nameLabel: Country of origin of the product or the service
descriptionLabel: A country of origin of the product or the service.

name: Country Origin Listname
nameLabel: Country of origin of the product or the service
descriptionLabel: A country of origin of the product or the service.

name: Tender Variant
descriptionLabel: The tender is a variant.

name: Unpublished Identifier
descriptionLabel: Identifier of the field that shall not be immediately published. Only fields concerning the Result value and groups of fields concerning the Tender and Procedure Lot Result can be unpublished. In the case of the European Parliament and Council Directive 2014/25/EU, the award criteria, the procurement procedure, certain dates and in certain cases information about the nature and quantity of a service can be unpublished as well.

descriptionLabel: The type of tenders or requests to participate received. The total number of tenders received shall be given. When a notice does not fall under Directive 2009/81/EC and is not about social or other specific services, the number of tenders received from micro, small and medium enterprises; the number of tenders received from tenderers registered in other European Economic Area countries and the number of tenders received from tenderers registered in countries outside of the European Economic Area shall also be given. All tenders shall be counted, regardless of whether they are admissible or inadmissible. For tenders submitted by a group of tenderers (e.g. a consortium), the tender shall be counted in the relevant category (e.g. SME) if the majority of the work is expected to be done by tenderers which fall within this category (e.g. they are SMEs).
